#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:655
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "On reaching the Final page, the plugin automatically validates the "
#| "values. If the numeric value column/s is/are highlighted in green, then "
#| "the validation was successful and all that is necessary is to click "
#| "<guilabel>Import CSV</guilabel> and control then passes to the main "
#| "&kappname; program. However, if the start and/or end lines are "
#| "incorrectly set, or if the wrong columns were selected, the highlighting "
#| "will be in red, and an error message will appear indicating where the "
#| "error lies. The user will then need to click <guilabel>Back</guilabel> to "
#| "get to the relevant page to correct the error."
msgid ""
"On reaching the Final page, the plugin automatically validates the values. "
"If the numeric value column/s is/are highlighted in green, then the "
"validation was successful and all that is necessary is to click "
"<guibutton>Import CSV</guibutton> and control then passes to the main "
"&kmymoney; program. However, if the start and/or end lines are incorrectly "
"set, or if the wrong columns were selected, the highlighting will be in red, "
"and an error message will appear indicating where the error lies. The user "
"will then need to click <guibutton>Back</guibutton> to get to the relevant "
"page to correct the error."
msgstr ""
"Pri dolasku na krajnju stranicu, dodatak će automatski validirati vaše "
"vrijednosti. Ukoliko je/su numerička vrijednost kolone/a označena/e zelenom "
"bojom, znači da je validacija bila uspješna i da je sve što je potrebno da "
"uradite klik na <guilabel>Uvezi CSV</guilabel> te će kontrolu preuzeti "
"glavni &kappname; program. Ipak, ukoliko je početna i/ili krajnja linija "
"pogrešno psotavljena, ili ukoliko su pogrešne kolone odabrane, biće označene "
"crvenom bojom, i poruka greške će se pojaviti indicirajući gdje je greška. "
"Korisnik onda mora kliknuti na <guilabel>Nazad</guilabel> kako bi došao do "
"odgovarajuće stranice i prepravio grešku."

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:666
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "It might also be that if debit and credit columns are in use, one of "
#| "those columns may legitimately contain no entries. This would mean that "
#| "that column has no decimal symbol present, and this would result in a "
#| "warning. If you see that this is the case, you may click either of the "
#| "<guilabel>Accept</guilabel> buttons (<guilabel>Accept this</guilabel> or "
#| "<guilabel>Accept all</guilabel>.)"
msgid ""
"It might also be that if debit and credit columns are in use, one of those "
"columns may legitimately contain no entries. This would mean that that "
"column has no decimal symbol present, and this would result in a warning. If "
"you see that this is the case, you may click either of the buttons to accept "
"(<guibutton>Accept this</guibutton> or <guibutton>Accept all</guibutton>.)"
msgstr ""
"Također može biti slučaj da se kolone za kredit i zaduženje koriste, te "
"jedna od ovih kolona može imati neispravan unos. Ovo bi značilo da kolona "
"nema decimalni znak prisutan i ovo bi rezultovalo upozorenjem. Ukoliko "
"primijetite ovo, možete kliknuti na bilo koje od <guilabel>Accept</guilabel> "
"dugmadi (<guilabel>Accept this</guilabel> ili<guilabel>Accept all</"
"guilabel>.)"

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid "Decimal Symbol"
msgstr "Decimalni simbol"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:675
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another possible problem might be that the selected decimal symbol is "
"incorrect. Selecting the symbol to match the data should clear that error. "
"Normally, you should not need to change this selection. Note that the "
"<guilabel>Decimal Symbol</guilabel> must be set to match your file, not your "
"locale. If your locale setting has a different value, conversion will be "
"seen to take place. The display of the file in the upper part of the window "
"will show numeric fields highlighted in green if the current setting "
"produces valid results, otherwise in red. The highlighting also reflects the "
"<guilabel>Start line</guilabel> and <guilabel>End line</guilabel> settings. "
"There could be warnings if any of the selected cells appear not to contain "
"the selected symbol."
msgstr ""
"Drugi mogući problem može biti ukoliko je odabrani decimalni simbol "
"pogrešan. Odabir simbola koji bi odgovarao podacima bi trebalo riješiti sve "
"probleme. Uobičajeno ne morate mijenjati ovaj odabir. Imajte na umu da "
"<guilabel>Decimalni Simbol</guilabel> mora biti podešen da odgovara vašoj "
"datoteci, a ne lokalnim podacima. Ukoliko su vaše lokalne postavke "
"drugačije, možete prmijetiti da će doći do promjene. Prikaz datoteke u "
"gornjem dijelu prozora će prikazati numeričko polje označeno zelenom bojom "
"ukoliko trenutne postavke pružaju ispravne rezultate, u suprotnom crvenom "
"bojom. Označavanje se također odnosi na <guilabel>Početna linija</guilabel> "
"i <guilabel>Krajnja linija</guilabel> postavke. Moguće je da će doći do "
"upozorenja ukoliko bilo koja od odabranih ćelija ne bude sadržavala odabrani "
"simbol."

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:690
#, no-c-format
msgid "Thousands Symbol"
msgstr "Simbol za oznaku hiljade"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:691
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This does not need to be selected, as it is set automatically based on the "
"<guilabel>Decimal Symbol</guilabel>. It is provided purely as a guide. In "
"addition, the selector will be inactive if none of the values to be imported "
"is greater or equal to 1000."
msgstr ""
"Ovo ne mora biti odabrano pošto je automatski postavljeno na "
"<guilabel>Decimal Symbol</guilabel>. Predviđeno je čisto kao vodič. Selektor "
"neće biti aktivan, ukoliko su sve vrijednosti koje se unose manje od 1000."

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:699
#, no-c-format
msgid "Import CSV"
msgstr "Unos CSV"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:700
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Clicking this button tells the plugin to actually import the data from "
#| "the file, based on the choices you have made above. &kappname; will "
#| "prompt you for the correct account into which to import the data."
msgid ""
"Clicking this button tells the plugin to actually import the data from the "
"file, based on the choices you have made above. &kmymoney; will prompt you "
"for the correct account into which to import the data."
msgstr ""
"Klikom na ovo dugme govorite dodatku da stvarno unese podatke iz datoteke, "
"bazirane na izborima koje ste vi donijeli iznad. &kappname; će vam prikazati "
"odgovarajući račun za koji će se unijeti podaci."

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:708
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make QIF File"
msgstr "Napravi QIF Datoteku"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:709
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This button gives you the ability, after the import has been completed, "
#| "to save the data from the csv file as a qif file, should you require one "
#| "for any reason. This was actually the original functionality that drove "
#| "the creation of this plugin. However, as &kappname; itself is now able to "
#| "export a qif file, the capability is now probably of little use and is "
#| "likely to be removed eventually."
msgid ""
"This button gives you the ability, after the import has been completed, to "
"save the data from the CSV file as a QIF file, should you require one for "
"any reason. This was actually the original functionality that drove the "
"creation of this plugin. However, as &kmymoney; itself is now able to export "
"a qif file, the capability is now probably of little use and is likely to be "
"removed eventually."
msgstr ""
"Ovo dugme vam daje mogućnost da nakon što je unos završen sačuvate podatke "
"iz csv datoteke u qif datoteku, ukoliko vam treba takva zbog bilo kakvog "
"razloga. Ovo je ustvari bila originalna funkcionalnost koja je dovela do "
"kreiranja ovog dodatka. Ipak, pošto &kappname; sada sam može eksportovati "
"qif datoteku, ova mogućnost se rijetko koristi i vjerovatno će se u "
"budućnosti u potpunosti izbaciti iz upotrebe."

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:719
#, no-c-format
msgid "Finishing up"
msgstr "Završavanje"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:720
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "For a <guilabel>Banking</guilabel> import, the plugin has finished, and "
#| "&kappname; will prompt you, as stated above, for the correct account into "
#| "which to import the data. For an <guilabel>Investment</guilabel> import, "
#| "however, a little more may be required. If, during import of a "
#| "transaction, the plugin finds no valid transaction type, it will display "
#| "the offending transaction, and the user may select a valid type to "
#| "substitute, depending on the combination of quantity, price, and amount "
#| "values. For every transaction, the plugin will validate the column "
#| "contents to ensure they match the action type. For instance, if a "
#| "quantity appears but no price or amount, it is assumed that the "
#| "transaction can be only an Add or Remove Shares. Or, if there is an "
#| "amount but no quantity or price, then a Dividend is assumed, etc.."
msgid ""
"For a <guilabel>Banking</guilabel> import, the plugin has finished, and "
"&kmymoney; will prompt you, as stated above, for the correct account into "
"which to import the data. For an <guilabel>Investment</guilabel> import, "
"however, a little more may be required. If, during import of a transaction, "
"the plugin finds no valid transaction type, it will display the offending "
"transaction, and the user may select a valid type to substitute, depending "
"on the combination of quantity, price, and amount values. For every "
"transaction, the plugin will validate the column contents to ensure they "
"match the action type. For instance, if a quantity appears but no price or "
"amount, it is assumed that the transaction can be only an Add or Remove "
"Shares. Or, if there is an amount but no quantity or price, then a Dividend "
"is assumed, &etc;"
msgstr ""
"Za <guilabel>Banking</guilabel> unos, dodatak je završio i &kappname; će vam "
"izbaciti odgovarajući račun za koji će se unijeti podaci. Za "
"<guilabel>Investment</guilabel> unos još neke informacije će se zahtijevati "
"od vas. Ukoliko prilikom unosa transakcije dodatak nije našao validan tip "
"transakcije, prikazaće vam odgovarajuću transakciju i korisnik potom može "
"odabrati korektan tip kao zamjenu u ovisnosti o kombinaciji količine, cijene "
"i iznosa vrijednosti. Za svaku transakciju dodatak će validirati sadržaj "
"kolone kako bi osigurao da odgovaraju tipu akcije. Npr., ukoliko se količina "
"pojavi, ali nema cijene ili iznosa, pretpostavlja se da transakcija može "
"biti samo Dodaj ili Ukloni Dionice. Ili ukoliko postoji iznos a nema "
"količine i cijene pretpostavlja se Dividenda itd.."

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:734
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you wish to save your settings, remember to click the "
#| "<guilabel>Finish</guilabel> button, and the plugin will then close."
msgid ""
"If you wish to save your settings, remember to click <guibutton>Finish</"
"guibutton>, and the plugin will then close."
msgstr ""
"Ukoliko želite spasiti svoje postavke, upamtite da morate kliknuti na "
"<guilabel>Završi</guilabel> dugme te će se dodatak potom zatvoriti."

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:740
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding Investment Activity Types"
msgstr "Dodavanje investicionih tipova aktivnosti"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:741
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you find that your investment statements keep including activity types "
#| "that are not recognized, just add them to the section in the resource "
#| "file. (See <link linkend=\"details.impexp.csv.config\">below</link> for "
#| "more details on this file.) For instance, in the [InvestmentSettings] "
#| "section of the file, the BuyParam field includes entries for Purchase, "
#| "Buy, New Inv, and Switch In. If you find a different one, add it to the "
#| "correct list and restart the plugin. You may notice that there are "
#| "similarities in the entries in different fields, and you may find that "
#| "the wrong activity type is being selected. The plugin checks these lists "
#| "in the following order: Shrsin, DivX, Reinvdiv, Brokerage, Buy, Sell, "
#| "Remove. Re-ordering the lists to suit this does not work as might be "
#| "expected, since the entries in the resource file get sorted into "
#| "alphabetical order. If the offending parameter is one you don't need, "
#| "just delete it from the file. If that is not possible, you may need to "
#| "edit your file before input."
msgid ""
"If you find that your investment statements keep including activity types "
"that are not recognized, just add them to the section in the resource file. "
"(See <link linkend=\"details.impexp.csv.config\">below</link> for more "
"details on this file.) For instance, in the <literal>[InvestmentSettings]</"
"literal> section of the file, the <literal>BuyParam</literal> field includes "
"entries for <literal>Purchase</literal>, <literal>Buy</literal>, "
"<literal>New Inv</literal>, and <literal>Switch In</literal>. If you find a "
"different one, add it to the correct list and restart the plugin. You may "
"notice that there are similarities in the entries in different fields, and "
"you may find that the wrong activity type is being selected. The plugin "
"checks these lists in the following order: <literal>Shrsin</literal>, "
"<literal>DivX</literal>, <literal>Reinvdiv</literal>, <literal>Brokerage</"
"literal>, <literal>Buy</literal>, <literal>Sell</literal>, and "
"<literal>Remove</literal>. Re-ordering the lists to suit this does not work "
"as might be expected, since the entries in the resource file get sorted into "
"alphabetical order. If the offending parameter is one you don't need, just "
"delete it from the file. If that is not possible, you may need to edit your "
"file before input."
msgstr ""
"Ukoliko primijetite da vaše izjave investicija nastavljaju uključivati "
"tipove aktivnosti koji se ne mogu prepoznati, samo ih dodajte u sekciju u "
"resursnoj datoteci. (Pogledajte <link linkend=\"details.impexp.csv.config"
"\">ispod</link> za više detalja o ovoj datoteci.) Npr., u "
"[InvesticionePostavke] sekciji datotek, BuyParam polje uključuje unose za "
"Purchase, Buy, New Inv, i Switch In. Ukoliko pronađete neku drugu, dodajte "
"ju u korektnu listu i restartujte dodatak. Možete primijetiti da postoje "
"sličnosti između unosa u različita polja i možda primijetite da je pogrešan "
"tip aktivnosti odabran. Dodatak provjerava ove liste u sljedećem "
"redoslijedu: Shrsin, DivX, Reinvdiv, Brokerage, Buy, Sell, Remove. "
"Preraspoređivanje listi kako vama odgovara ne radi kako bi se i očekivalo, "
"pošto se unosi u resursnoj datoteci sortiraju po abecedi. Ukoliko vam "
"odabrani parametar ne treba, samo ga izbrišite iz datoteke. Ukoliko to nije "
"moguće, možda morate editovati svoju datoteku prije unosa."

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:761
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuration of CSV importer plugin"
msgstr "Konfiguracija CSV importer dodatka"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:762
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "A well-known drawback of QIF format is that it is a fairly loose format. "
#| "With CSV files, there is this same problem, only more so, in that there "
#| "is no agreed standard at all. With investment files, in particular, there "
#| "is much more scope for variation in specifying the different types of "
#| "activities represented in the data. The plugin handles this by listing "
#| "these activity types in a resource file, called csvimporterrc. The "
#| "location of this file depends on your distribution. It will usually be "
#| "located in ~/.kde4/share/config/, or in ~/.kde/... instead. Using this "
#| "resource file allows the user to add an activity type that the developer "
#| "had not encountered. If the file does not exist when the importer first "
#| "runs, the plugin will create a default version, containing a few of the "
#| "more obvious descriptions."
msgid ""
"A well-known drawback of QIF format is that it is a fairly loose format. "
"With CSV files, there is this same problem, only more so, in that there is "
"no agreed standard at all. With investment files, in particular, there is "
"much more scope for variation in specifying the different types of "
"activities represented in the data. The plugin handles this by listing these "
"activity types in a resource file, called <filename>csvimporterrc</"
"filename>. The location of this file depends on your operating system or "
"distribution. On a &Linux; system, this will be <filename class=\"directory"
"\">$KDEHOME/share/config</filename> where <envar>$KDEHOME</envar> is usually "
"<filename class=\"directory\">.config</filename> within your home folder. If "
"you are migrating from a version of &kmymoney; prior to 5.0, the old "
"location of <envar>$KDEHOME</envar> was <filename class=\"directory\">.kde4</"
"filename>, also within your home folder. Using this resource file allows the "
"user to add an activity type that the developer had not encountered. If the "
"file does not exist when the importer first runs, it will create a default "
"version, containing a few of the more obvious descriptions."
msgstr ""
"Veoma poznata mana QIF formata je da je veoma labav format. Sa CSV "
"datotekama, postoji isti problem, s tim što uopšte ne postoji dogovoreni "
"standard. Sa investicionim datotekama posebno, postoji mnogo veći interval "
"varijacija u specificiranju različitih tipova aktivnosti predstavljenih u "
"podacima. Dodatak upravlja ovim pomoću izlistavanja tipova aktivnosti u "
"resursnu datoteku, nazvanu scvimporterrc. Lokacija ove datoteke ovisi o "
"vašoj distribuciji. Najčešće će biti locirana u ~/.kde4/share/config/, ili u "
"~/.kde/... . Upotreba ove resursne datoteke omogućava korisniku da doda "
"tipove aktivnosti s kojima se developer nije susreo. Ukoliko datoteka ne "
"postoji prilikom prvog pokretanja importera, dodatak će kreirati unaprijed "
"definisanu verziju, koja će sadržavati par očitih opisa."

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:780
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "A number of sample csv files are provided (in the kmymoney/contrib/"
#| "csvimporter/ folder in the source tree) in the hope that they may help. "
#| "For example, in the investment sample, an activity type is "
#| "\"ReInvestorContract Buy : ReInvested Units\". In the validation process, "
#| "the first successful match is on the ReInv in ReInvestorContract Buy, so "
#| "the transaction therefore gets classed as Reinvdiv, even though Buy also "
#| "is mentioned. Another example which has been observed is an activity type "
#| "of Reinvest even though the transaction included neither price nor "
#| "amount, but only a quantity, so that needed to be treated as Add Shares, "
#| "or Shrsin."
msgid ""
"A number of sample CSV files are provided (in the <filename class=\"directory"
"\"> kmymoney/contrib/csvimporter/</filename> folder in the source tree) in "
"the hope that they may help. For example, in the investment sample, an "
"activity type is \"<literal>ReInvestorContract Buy : ReInvested Units</"
"literal>\". In the validation process, the first successful match is on the "
"<literal>ReInv</literal> in <literal>ReInvestorContract Buy</literal>, so "
"the transaction therefore gets classed as <literal>Reinvdiv</literal>, even "
"though <literal>Buy</literal> also is mentioned. Another example which has "
"been observed is an activity type of <literal>Reinvest</literal> even though "
"the transaction included neither price nor amount, but only a quantity, so "
"that needed to be treated as <literal>Add Shares</literal>, or "
"<literal>Shrsin</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Pružen je niz CSV datoteka (u kmymoney/contrib/csvimporter/ direktoriju u "
"izvornom stablu) u nadi da će vam biti od neke pomoći. Npr., u investicionom "
"primjeru, tip aktivnosti je \"ReInvestorContract Buy : ReInvested Units\". "
"Uprocesu validacije, prvo uspješno povezivanje je na Reinv u "
"ReInvestorContract Buy pa se zato transakcija klasificira kao Reinvdiv iako "
"je i Buy pomenuto. Još jedan primjer koji se posmatra je tip aktivnosti "
"Reinvest iako transakcija nije uključila ni cijenu ni iznos, nego samo "
"količinu, što je potrebno da bi bila tretirana kao Add Shares ili Shrsin."

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:794
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "When this plugin was created, only a few investment formats had been seen "
#| "as examples, and it may well be that you will encounter one which cannot "
#| "be handled correctly. If you find such a file, please send a suitable "
#| "example (edited to remove or replace personal information) to the "
#| "&kappname; user list &userlist; or developer list &devlist;, the "
#| "developer will do his best to modify the plugin to handle it."
msgid ""
"When this plugin was created, only a few investment formats had been seen as "
"examples, and it may well be that you will encounter one which cannot be "
"handled correctly. If you find such a file, please send a suitable example "
"(edited to remove or replace personal information) to the &kmymoney; user "
"list &userlist; or developer list &devlist;, the developer will do his best "
"to modify the plugin to handle it."
msgstr ""
"Kada je ovaj dodatak napravljen, samo je nekoliko investicionih formata bilo "
"dodano kao primjer i moguće je da ćete doći u susret sa nekim kojim se ne "
"može upravljati ispravno. Ukoliko pronađete takvu datoteku, molimo vas da "
"pošaljete odgovarajući primjer (editovan kako biste uklonili ili zamijenili "
"bilo kakve lične podatke) u &kappname; korisničku listu &userlist; ili "
"developersku listu &devlist;, developer će uraditi najbolje što može kako bi "
"modificirao dodatak da radi i sa takvim tipom."

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:803
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "CSV Importer Plugin"
msgid "CSV Importer configuration dialog"
msgstr "CSV Importer dodatak"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:804
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally, there are a few other items which may be configured in a dialog "
"invoked through the <link linkend=\"details.settings.plugins.csvimporter"
"\">CSV Importer configuration dialog</link>, which can be invoked from the "
"Plugins page of the main KMyMoney configuration dialog. This includes which "
"items will be autodetected by the importer and which profile will be used if "
"you do have the importer export a QIF file, as mentioned above."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:820
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "CSV Importer Plugin"
msgid "CSV Exporter"
msgstr "CSV Importer dodatak"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:822
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To import a CSV file, choose the importer from the menu bar: "
#| "<menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Import</"
#| "guimenuitem><guimenuitem>CSV...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. If CSV does "
#| "not show up under Import, you do not have the CSV Importer Plugin "
#| "installed correctly. Please see the previous section."
msgid ""
"To export data to a CSV file, choose the <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu> "
"<guisubmenu>Export</guisubmenu> <guimenuitem>CSV...</guimenuitem> </"
"menuchoice> menu item. The dialog which appears gives you a number of "
"choices which control the data to be exported."
msgstr ""
"Da biste unijeli CSV datoteku, odaberite importer iz meni bara: "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Import</"
"guimenuitem><guimenuitem>CSV...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Ukoliko se CSV "
"ne pojavi pod Import, nemate CSV importer dodatak korektno instaliran. "
"Molimo vas pogledajte prethodnu sekciju."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:830
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>csv exporter</screeninfo>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:836
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "CSV Import Wizard: Separators"
msgid "<phrase>csv exporter</phrase>"
msgstr "CSV Import Čarobnjak: Razdvajači"

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:841
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please note that an exported CSV file can include data from only one account."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:845
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify the name of the exported CSV file either by entering the complete "
"path in the <guilabel>File to export to</guilabel> field, or by clicking "
"<guilabel>Browse</guilabel> and navigating to it in the Save File dialog. "
"Choose which account to export with the <guilabel>Account to export</"
"guilabel> dropdown."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:852
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The time period of data exported is controlled by the <guilabel>Date Range</"
"guilabel> <guilabel>Start on</guilabel> and <guilabel>End on</guilabel> date "
"fields. The default values represent the complete date range of your entire "
"data file, and they are adjusted when you select an account to export."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:859
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, the <guilabel>Field Separator</guilabel> is a comma, but you can "
"also choose to use a tab or semicolon."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:864
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you check the <guilabel>Contents to Export</guilabel> <guilabel>Account</"
"guilabel> radio button, then the data exported will be the transactions from "
"the specified account and date range. However, if you select the "
"<guilabel>Categories</guilabel> radio button, then the exported file will "
"contain one row for each category which has been defined. For top level "
"categories, the category name is shown, and an <quote>I</quote> or <quote>E</"
"quote> is shown to indicate whether the Category is Income or Expense. For "
"non top-level categories, the parent category is also shown."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-impexp-csv.docbook:875
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The exporter will output a set of columns appropriate for the type of "
"account being exported."
msgstr ""

